{
  "texts": [
    "Do we want everybody to become software developers?",
    "Of course not.",
    "Even only some basic programming skills can already be very useful, allowing a researcher to become more selfreliant and produce more reliable and reproducible results in less time.",
    "The authors have time and again seen participants of their introduction to programming courses make such progress.",
    "The level of programming skills that is perhaps easiest to obtain is the ability to take code from the Internet and to be able to set up an environment to get it to run."
  ]
}